h3#overview Overview
p
	a(href="/mesh") Chico Mesh
	|  provides a set of CSS columns that makes the laying out of a website easy and fast.

h3#download Download
p
	| It isn't part of the CSS core, that's why you have to download the file and reference it on your HTML document:
ul.ch-list
	li
		strong Production
		|  (Minified): 
		a(href="/versions/latest/chico-mesh-min.css", target="_blank") chico-mesh-min.css
	li
		strong Development 
		|  (Uncompressed): 
		a(href="/versions/latest/chico-mesh.css", target="_blank") chico-mesh.css

h3#classnames Class names
p
	| Each column is expressed in fractions that represent a width percent of the content.
p
	| The class names replace the bar 
	code /
	|  in the fraction by a dash 
	code -
	| :
ul.ch-list
	li
		code 50%
		|  same as 
		code 1/2
		|  same as class name
		code ch-g1-2

	li
		code 75%
		|  same as 
		code 3/4
		|  same as class name
		code ch-g3-4
	li
		code 20%
		|  same as 
		code 1/5
		|  same as class name
		code ch-g1-5

h3#gutters Gutters
p
	| The grids have neither padding nor margin. To be able to get the gutters, you have to assign a margin 
	strong to the element that's inside the grid
	| . For that, we defined 3 classes that create a margin to the inner element:
ul.ch-list
	li
		code ch-leftcolumn
		| : assign it to the left element.
	li
		code ch-centercolumn
		| : assign it to a centered element.
	li
		code ch-rightcolumn
		| : assign it to the right element.

h3#rounding Rounding
p
	| The 1/3 and 1/6 column widths have infinite or too long decimals. To fix this issue, we created a grid with the extra percent you need to round to 100%.
ul.ch-list
	li
		code 33.34%
		|  same as
		code 1/3
		|  same as class name
		code ch-g1-3r
	li
		code 16.66%
		|  same as
		code 1/6
		|  same as class name
		code ch-g1-6r
p
	| If you need 3 columns of equal widths, one of the 3 grids have to be 
	code ch-g1-3r
	| , like this:
pre
	| <div class="ch-g1-3">
	| 	<div class="ch-leftcolumn">
	| 		33,33%
	| 	</div>
	| </div>
	| <div class="ch-g1-3r">
	| 	<div class="ch-centercolumn">
	| 		33,34%
	| 	</div>
	| </div>
	| <div class="ch-g1-3">
	| 	<div class="ch-rightcolumn">
	| 		33,33%
	| 	</div>
	| </div> 
p
	| Same thing happens with 1/6: one of the 6 grids have to be 
	code ch-g1-6r
	| .

